Current response from api `/_nodes/_all/clear` is below:

```
{
    "cluster_name": "test",
    "nodes": {
         "47UWFACERJuqujyi60jQMA": {
                 "name":"test-1",
                 "transport_address":"inet[/10.10.0.1:9300]",
                 "host": "test1",
                 "ip": "10.10.0.1",
                 "version":"1.7.2",
                "build":"e43676b",
                "http_address":"inet[/10.10.0.1:9200]",
                "attributes":{
                     "max_local_storage_nodes":"1",
                     "rack":"rack0","master":"true"
                }
         }
}
```

The format of  `transport_address` and `http_address` has changed. Do as the old way, it will lead `ValueError` when call `int(port)`.

One mode definition file can contain different modes, e.g. clike includes C, C++, C#, Java, and a few others. We need to use the mime type to distinguish which one we want.

Closes gh-2737

@gnestor can we sneak this fix into 5.1?
